title: Brown recluse
description: While the brown recluse is not known to be aggressive, their bites can become swollen, red and last for about three weeks

title: Bullet ants
description: The bullet ant is known to have the most painful sting of any insect

title: Deer tick
description: This tiny insect can carry Lyme disease, and once infected, a person can exhibit symptoms such as a rash and fever

title: Kissing Bug
description: This bug is found widespread in the Americas and can carry Chagas Disease

title: Tsetse Fly
description: When bitten by the Sub-Saharan nations' tsetse fly, a parasite carried by this insect travels into the human body
